---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import TrustStrip from '../components/TrustStrip.astro';
import CTABlock from '../components/CTABlock.astro';
import { BASE } from '../data/business';

const title = 'About Sorn Handyman Services | Fraser & Aidan, father & son, East Ayrshire';
const description = '20+ years on the tools (Fraser) plus a qualified mechanical engineer & plumber (Aidan). Family-run, insured, 24/7 across East Ayrshire. Learn how we work.';
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description} canonicalPath="/about/">
  <Breadcrumbs trail={[{ name: 'Home', href: `${BASE}/` }, { name: 'About' }]} />
  <article class="container-x py-12 max-w-3xl prose-sorn">
    <span class="eyebrow">Who we are</span>
    <h1 class="mt-3 font-serif text-5xl font-black text-navy-900">Father and son. One van. One phone number. Always on.</h1>

    <p class="mt-6 text-lg">
      Sorn Handyman Services is Fraser and Aidan — a father-and-son trade based in the village of Sorn, in the heart of East Ayrshire. We cover the villages of the Irvine and Ayr valleys from Kilmarnock to Troon and everywhere between, seven days a week, twenty-four hours a day.
    </p>

    <h2>Fraser — 20+ years on the tools</h2>
    <p>
      Fraser has been a tradesman for over two decades. Joinery is his first love — you can tell by the way he sets a door into a cottage frame that was cut before central heating was invented — but he has picked up every adjacent skill the job demands: tiling, rendering, slating, slabbing, decking, and the hundred small repairs that sit between trades.
    </p>

    <h2>Aidan — qualified mechanical engineer & plumber</h2>
    <p>
      Aidan came up through the engineering route — a qualified mechanical engineer and a qualified plumber. He handles the water side of the job, the flat-pack builds that need a steady hand with an Allen key, and the spreadsheet paperwork that keeps the business running. If the quote is written, Aidan wrote it; if the kitchen tap stopped dripping at 3am, Aidan was the one with the wrench.
    </p>

    <h2>Why 24/7?</h2>
    <p>
      Because problems don\u2019t respect office hours. A leaking pipe at 11pm is not waiting till Monday. A cracked pane on Christmas Eve is not a January job. When we started this business we made a deal with ourselves: one of us answers every call. The phone number in the van is a real phone, and one of us always has it.
    </p>
    <p>
      Non-urgent call at 2am? We book you in for first light and get back to sleep. Flooding kitchen at 2am? We are in the van. Either way, you get a real voice and a plan in thirty seconds.
    </p>

    <h2>How we quote</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Photo over WhatsApp for a <strong>ballpark within the hour</strong>.</li>
      <li>Site visit and <strong>written, fixed-price quote</strong> for anything over £200.</li>
      <li>No call-out fee. We only charge once we\u2019re on the tools.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Insured and accountable</h2>
    <p>
      £2m public liability insurance. Written quotes. Bank transfer or card. No cash pressure. We send a line-by-line invoice on completion and a photo-log of the finished job for anything we can stand back from.
    </p>

    <h2>Local, not hypothetical</h2>
    <p>
      We live here. Our kids walk the same streets, our parents drink in the same pubs, our vans park on the same roads. A handyman who is four miles away and who cares what the neighbours think is a different handyman to one who\u2019s dispatched from an algorithm.
    </p>
    <p>
      If you have a job, call <a href="tel:+447900255876">07900 255876</a> — or message us on WhatsApp — and whoever is closer will be there first.
    </p>
  </article>
  <TrustStrip />
  <CTABlock heading="Any job. Any hour. One call." />
</BaseLayout>
